  <h1 class="page-title">Data &amp; Methodology</h1>

  <main>
    <div>
      <section id="data">
        <h2 class="section-title">Data Collection &amp; Preparation</h2>

        <div class="card">
          <span class="pill">Data Sources</span>
          <p>
            We use open data on population, unemployment, and businesses to
            understand economic patterns in San Diego.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Population and unemployment statistics over time.</li>
            <li>Business registrations, openings, and closures.</li>
            <li>Business location data for spatial analysis.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <span class="pill">Preprocessing</span>
          <ul>
            <li>Cleaning missing values and inconsistent entries.</li>
            <li>Encoding categorical fields and selecting key features.</li>
            <li>Aggregating data by neighborhood and time period.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="analysis">
        <h2 class="section-title">Exploratory Analysis</h2>

        <div class="card">
          <span class="pill">Spatial Mapping</span>
          <h3>Where are communities at risk?</h3>
          <p>
            We map business locations and closures to identify hotspots where
            communities may be losing jobs and vital services.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Cluster of closures by neighborhood.</li>
            <li>Overlap with high unemployment or vulnerable populations.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <span class="pill">Time-Series Trends</span>
          <h3>How do things change over time?</h3>
          <p>
            We analyze trends in business creation and closure, and compare
            them to unemployment trends to anticipate risk.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Changes in openings vs. closures by year.</li>
            <li>Correlation with unemployment spikes.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="ml">
        <h2 class="section-title">Machine Learning Models</h2>

        <div class="card">
          <span class="pill">Predictive Modeling</span>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Logistic Regression</strong> – Estimate the probability
              that a business will close based on its characteristics.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Random Forest</strong> – Improve predictive accuracy and
              capture non-linear relationships and interactions.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <span class="pill">Clustering</span>
          <p>
            We group businesses into clusters (by sector, size, or geography)
            to identify distinct ecosystems within San Diego.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Neighborhood-based business ecosystems.</li>
            <li>Sector clusters (e.g., hospitality, retail, services).</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <span class="pill">Link to Outcomes</span>
          <p>
            Model results guide where to prioritize training programs, policy
            interventions, and support services to prevent closures and reduce
            unemployment.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>

